20/02/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Visiting Skopje Friday (18 February), Kosovo's main opposition leader Hashim Thaci said that the process of demarcating the joint border with Macedonia should be implemented only after Kosovo's status is resolved.
Thaci, who was in the Macedonian capital for a roundtable on Kosovo-related issues, held informal talks with Macedonian Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski, who has called for resolving the border issue as soon as possible.
(Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik, Vest - 19/02/05;
A1 TV - 18/02/05)
